<item>
            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-607] Filtered Messages Require ACK from Client Causes User Being Throttled Incorrectly Forever</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-607</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In current FIFODeliveryManager, once a message is filtered in ActiveSubscriberState#messageScanned(), it just call ActiveSubscriberState#sendingFinished() and wait client&apos;s acknowledgement. However, the message isn&apos;t being delivered to client side, and once the number of such filtered messages larger than the delivery window size, the user cannot receive messages anymore!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12643866">BOOKKEEPER-607</key>
            <summary>Filtered Messages Require ACK from Client Causes User Being Throttled Incorrectly Forever</summary>
